I"•<p>If visitors with a custom parameter appended to the URL (e.g. <code class="highlighter-rouge">?noauth=1</code>) shall be able to bypass a basic auth login, this is how the <em>Nginx</em> site config should look like:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>...
# set the default: activate basic auth
set $auth "Restricted";

# if get parameter noauth=1, bypass basic auth and set cookie
if ($arg_noauth = 1) {
  set $auth "off";
  add_header Set-Cookie "noauth=1";
}

# if cookie is set, bypass basic auth
if ($cookie_noauth = 1) {
  set $auth "off";
}

auth_basic $auth;
...
</code></pre></div></div>

